{
  "stem": "11801.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How would I know what I lacked?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, what did I know about being brought up in a home with a mother and a father and maybe some siblings and other relatives around?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I couldn't compare it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't compare my life to somebody who had a more quote-unquote 'normal' childhood.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I really, you know, was at a loss as to how to handle my childhood, vis-a-vis that of a what we might call a normal person.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It came-- it hit me the first time, when my oldest daughter was born.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All of a sudden, I had to be a mother, and my husband had to be a father.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what did I know about being a mother?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, when you have a small baby, it's easy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The baby has to be taken care of.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You learn how to take care of a baby.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You learn how to bathe a baby, how to feed it, how to love it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the easy part.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When my daughter turned eight-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when my oldest daughter turned eight I almost had a nervous-- I almost had  a nervous breakdown.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Because it-- [CRYING] then it hit me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[CRYING] Sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It hit me that [DRINKS] I was at a loss.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't know how to be a mother to an eight-- to an eight-year-old, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that's when my normal childhood stopped.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I no longer had a role model now.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I never talked about this to anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was only going on in my own head, and I was-- it disturbed me, and it-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] but I never had, felt the need to discuss it with anyone, because there was no opportunity.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
